<section class="product-tabs" aria-labelledby="product-tabs-title" data-product-tabs>
  <header class="product-tabs-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">System paths</p>
    <h2 id="product-tabs-title">Deployment and prototype context</h2>
    <p>This project evolved from a thesis prototype that validated a selected product-grading concept into a private-source deployment-oriented system designed for configurable conveyor grading workflows. The later system emphasizes GUI- and configuration-driven operation, replaceable trained YOLO weights, adjustable class and mask settings, and a top-view hardware direction designed for higher object throughput.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="product-tab-list" role="tablist" aria-label="Product Grading system context">
    <button
      id="deployment-system-tab"
      type="button"
      role="tab"
      aria-selected="true"
      aria-controls="deployment-system-panel"
      tabindex="0"
    >
      Deployment System &amp; GUI
    </button>
    <button
      id="masters-prototype-tab"
      type="button"
      role="tab"
      aria-selected="false"
      aria-controls="masters-prototype-panel"
      tabindex="-1"
    >
      Master’s Prototype
    </button>
  </div>

  <section
    id="deployment-system-panel"
    class="product-tab-panel"
    role="tabpanel"
    aria-labelledby="deployment-system-tab"
    tabindex="0"
  >
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>A private-source AI application system for conveyor product grading workflows. The deployment-oriented version focuses on practical operation, configurable grading logic, model-swapping flexibility, multi-source input handling, and a GUI-driven workflow for preparing, launching, monitoring, and reviewing inference runs.</p>

    <h3>Detailed Scope</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Supports video, camera, and RealSense-oriented input workflows.</li>
      <li>Tested with Jetson Orin Nano + Intel RealSense D435 as the documented hardware context.</li>
      <li>Uses YOLO-based visual inference at a high level without exposing private model internals.</li>
      <li>Designed to support different conveyor-object grading tasks by swapping trained YOLO weights and adjusting GUI- and configuration-driven settings.</li>
      <li>Configuration covers class definitions, mask-related settings, grading logic, input-source selection, and runtime execution parameters.</li>
      <li>GUI pages and controls cover runtime setup, source selection, model and inference configuration, class and mask customization, grading setup, launch and stop control, runtime logs, and result navigation.</li>
      <li>The current direction shifts toward a top-view workflow and revised hardware setup designed for higher object throughput than the earlier multi-view prototype; this is a design direction rather than a verified performance result.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Boundaries / Pending Evidence</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Source code remains private, and no private runtime repository is linked.</li>
      <li>Public screenshots and operator-workflow evidence remain pending review.</li>
      <li>Verified performance measurements remain pending public review.</li>
      <li>Internal model details, raw product images, model weights, and private runtime configuration are not exposed.</li>
      <li>Vendor-specific details and command or protocol details remain excluded.</li>
      <li>The page does not characterize the system as deployment-complete or certified for production use.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section
    id="masters-prototype-panel"
    class="product-tab-panel"
    role="tabpanel"
    aria-labelledby="masters-prototype-tab"
    tabindex="0"
    hidden
  >
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>A thesis-oriented product grading prototype focused on validating the computer-vision concept and building the model-training workflow behind the system. The prototype emphasized how the model and dataset were constructed, rather than how the final workflow would be operated by users.</p>

    <h3>Detailed Scope</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>A graduate research prototype focused on one selected product-grading scenario rather than a configurable multi-object deployment workflow.</li>
      <li>Used top, front, and back views to capture more complete object characteristics.</li>
      <li>Used YOLO-based detection and segmentation while emphasizing dataset construction, annotation, preprocessing, and model training.</li>
      <li>Combined synthetic data with model-assisted annotation methods, including SAM-assisted labeling and pseudo-labeling at a high level, alongside preprocessing and augmentation.</li>
      <li>Tested with Jetson Orin Nano + Intel RealSense D435 as the documented hardware context.</li>
      <li>Established a model-development and product-grading foundation that informed the later runtime and GUI direction.</li>
      <li>Compared with the prototype, the later system shifts from a fixed research scenario toward a configurable top-view workflow, GUI-driven operation, and replaceable trained-model and configuration support.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Boundaries / Pending Evidence</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The prototype is distinct from the deployment-oriented runtime, and its results are not used as deployment-system benchmarks.</li>
      <li>Raw datasets, private images, annotation files, and model weights remain excluded.</li>
      <li>Vendor-sensitive details remain excluded.</li>
      <li>Any future thesis metrics would require clear experiment-context wording and remain separate from later-system evidence.</li>
      <li>The prototype is presented as graduate research, not as evidence of production deployment.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <noscript>
    <style>.product-tab-panel[hidden] { display: block; }</style>
    <p class="product-tabs-noscript">JavaScript is unavailable, so both sections are shown in document order.</p>
  </noscript>
</section>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-product-tabs]').forEach((container) => {
    const tabs = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[role="tab"]'));
    const panels = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[role="tabpanel"]'));

    const activateTab = (activeTab: HTMLButtonElement, moveFocus = true) => {
      tabs.forEach((tab) => {
        const isActive = tab === activeTab;
        tab.setAttribute('aria-selected', String(isActive));
        tab.tabIndex = isActive ? 0 : -1;
      });

      panels.forEach((panel) => {
        panel.hidden = panel.id !== activeTab.getAttribute('aria-controls');
      });

      if (moveFocus) activeTab.focus();
    };

    tabs.forEach((tab, index) => {
      tab.addEventListener('click', () => activateTab(tab));
      tab.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
        let nextIndex = index;

        if (event.key === 'ArrowRight' || event.key === 'ArrowDown') nextIndex = (index + 1) % tabs.length;
        if (event.key === 'ArrowLeft' || event.key === 'ArrowUp') nextIndex = (index - 1 + tabs.length) % tabs.length;
        if (event.key === 'Home') nextIndex = 0;
        if (event.key === 'End') nextIndex = tabs.length - 1;

        if (nextIndex !== index) {
          event.preventDefault();
          activateTab(tabs[nextIndex]);
        }
      });
    });

    const selectedTab = tabs.find((tab) => tab.getAttribute('aria-selected') === 'true');
    if (selectedTab) activateTab(selectedTab, false);
  });
</script>
